Nord theme (LTR): transparent circular favicons.

The default Nord theme places a light background (var(--text-accent))
behind feed favicons with border-radius: 4px. This creates a visible
light rectangle behind transparent or circular favicons, particularly
noticeable with YouTube channel avatars. This patch removes the
background and makes the clipping circular.

Companion: freshrss-nord-favicons-rtl.patch applies the identical
change to nord.rtl.css. They're split so each file can be applied,
skipped, or detected as already-applied independently.

--- a/p/themes/Nord/nord.css
+++ b/p/themes/Nord/nord.css
@@ -471,8 +471,8 @@
 }

 img.favicon {
-	background: var(--text-accent);
-	border-radius: 4px;
+	background: none;
+	border-radius: 50%;
 }

